                только ‘кисть’ (см. <bibl><ref target="#src_Сл."/></bibl>), но вся ‘рука’; ср. также
                у %sЯлгузидзе%s <mentioned xml:lang="os"
                        ><lang/><w>ærddæ</w><gloss><q>руки</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                        target="#src_Матфей"/><biblScope>%i27%i 24</biblScope></bibl>). Это же слово
                употреблялось в значении ‘оглобля’, как то свидетельствует д. <ref type="xr"
                    target="#entry_ar"/> ‘оглобля’, а также <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ardwan"/>
                ‘рашпиль’ и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærmbos"/> ‘гужовка’</note>
            <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">. Such words as <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dælarm"
                /> ‘under one's arm’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ræmbyn"/> ‘elbow’, <ref
                    type="xr" target="#entry_ælmærīn"/> ‘cubit’, <ref type="xr"
                    target="#entry_ærmæftaw"/> ‘weather-vane’, indicate that %iarm%i meant not only
                ‘hand’ (see <bibl><ref target="#src_Сл."/></bibl>), but the whole ‘arm’; cf. also
                    <mentioned xml:lang="os"
                    ><lang/><w>ærddæ</w><gloss><q>hands</q></gloss></mentioned> by %sYalguzidze%s
                        (<bibl><ref target="#src_Матфей"/><biblScope>%i27%i 24</biblScope></bibl>).
                The same word was used in the sense ‘shaft’, as is proven by Digor <ref type="xr"
                    target="#entry_ar"/> ‘shaft’, and also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ardwan"/>
                ‘rasp’ and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærmbos"/> ‘tug’</note>
        </re>
