    <etym xml:lang="ru">Как большинство анатомических терминов (см. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_kom"/> и др.), относится к старому иранскому фонду: <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>arm</w></mentioned> (в литературе не засвидетельствовано),
            <mentioned xml:lang="zza"><lang/><w>ärmä</w><gloss><q>плечо</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. IV, стр.
                280</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p.
        280</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                ><lang/><w>yurm</w><gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
                ><lang/><w>yārmё</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"
                /><biblScope>II 59</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="tly"
                    ><lang/><w>ām</w><gloss><q>плечо</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="tly"><w/><gloss><q>предплечье</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*arm(’rm)</w></mentioned> в <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>’ps’rm</w><gloss><q>имеющий связанные за спиной
            руки</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Gramm._sogd."/><biblScope>II
                90</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><lang/><w>er-</w><gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>X 585</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>arəma-</w><gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>īrmа́-</w><gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><w>armukn</w><gloss><q>локоть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>рамо</w><gloss><q>плечо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="prg"><lang/><w>irmo</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"
                ><lang/><w>arms</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><lang/><w>Arm</w><gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>armus</w><gloss><q>лопатка</q></gloss></mentioned>. В значении
        ‘оглобля’ — <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>armai</w></mentioned>. Для истории
        осетинского языка представляет интерес, что понятия ‘рука’, ‘нога’, ‘рот’ имеют наряду с
        иранскими наименованиями (%iarm%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kom"/>) параллельный ряд
        неиранских, идущих из кавказского субстрата (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ʒyx"/>), причем
        последние в самостоятельном употреблении почти вытеснили первые, тогда как в старых сложных
        словах и сочетаниях встречаются почти исключительно первые (иранские).%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>17, 78, 117, 154, 197</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Like most anatomical terms (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kom"/> etc.),
        it belongs to the old Iranian stock: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>arm</w></mentioned>
        (not attested in literature), <mentioned xml:lang="zza"
                    ><lang/><w>ärmä</w><gloss><q>shoulder</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. IV, стр.
                280</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p.
        280</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                ><lang/><w>yurm</w><gloss><q>hand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
                ><lang/><w>yārmё</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"
                /><biblScope>II 59</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="tly"
                    ><lang/><w>ām</w><gloss><q>shoulder</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="tly"><w/><gloss><q>forearm</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*arm(’rm)</w></mentioned> in <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>’ps’rm</w><gloss><q>with the hands tied behind</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Gramm._sogd."/><biblScope>II 90</biblScope></bibl>),
            <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>er-</w><gloss><q>hand</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>X 585</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>arəma-</w><gloss><q>hand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>īrmа́-</w><gloss><q>hand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><w>armukn</w><gloss><q>elbow</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>рамо</w><gloss><q>shoulder</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="prg"><lang/><w>irmo</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"
                ><lang/><w>arms</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><lang/><w>Arm</w><gloss><q>hand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>armus</w><gloss><q>shoulder-blade</q></gloss></mentioned>. As
        for the meaning ‘shaft’, see <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>armai</w></mentioned>. For
        the history of Ossetic, it is of interest that the concepts ‘hand’, ‘leg’, ‘mouth’, along
        with Iranian names (%iarm%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kom"/>) have a parallel row of
        non-Iranian words coming from the Caucasian substratum (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ʒyx"
        />), and the latter words almost forced out the former words in independent use, while in
        the old compound words and collocations there are almost exclusively the first (Iranian)
                words.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
        50</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
            /><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>17,
                78, 117, 154, 197</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
